{The position is also very similar to the previous one. After f2-f4, White's
attack develops easily.} 15. Nf5 ({White can also start with} 15. f4 {, and
after} exf4 16. Rxf4 Kh8 17. Rcf1 f6 18. Nf5 Qf8 19. h4 $1 {continue with the
same attacking pattern.}) 15... Qf6 (15... Qf8 {is not any better.} 16. f4 Re6
$5 (16... exf4 17. Qxf4 Rac8 (17... Ne5 18. d4 Ng6 19. Qxc7) 18. Nh6+ gxh6 19.
Qg4+) 17. fxe5 Nxe5 18. d4 Ng6 19. Qxc7 Rxe4 20. Qxb7 Nf4 21. Ng3 Rxd4 22. c3
Rd3 23. Rxf4 Rxg3 24. Rcf1 f6 25. Qxc6 $18) 16. f4 Qg6 {Hoping to stop the
attack by trading queens.} (16... exf4 17. Rxf4 Kh8 18. Rcf1 Qxb2 {would be
met by the simple combination} 19. Qxg7+ Qxg7 20. Nxg7 Kxg7 21. Rxf7+ Kg8 22.
Rxd7 {, with an easily winning endgame.}) 17. Qh4 Qf6 18. Qg3 Qg6 19. Qh2 {
Of course White should reject the offer.} ({But more precise is} 19. Qe3 $5)
19... c5 20. Rf3 $1 Qc6 ({More combative was} 20... c4 $5 21. b3 (21. Rg3 $6
Qb6+ 22. Kh1 g6 $132) 21... cxd3 22. cxd3 Qb6+ 23. Kh1 c5 {, and now White has
to find} 24. b4 $3 cxb4 (24... Qxb4 25. Qg3 g6 26. Rcf1 $18) (24... Rac8 25.
Qg3 Qf6 26. bxc5 Rxc5 27. Rxc5 Nxc5 28. fxe5) 25. Qg3 g6 (25... Qg6 26. Rc7 $1)
26. Nh6+ Kg7 27. Ng4 h5 28. Ne3 exf4 29. Rxf4 Rad8 (29... Ne5 30. d4) 30. Nf5+
Kf8 31. Nd6 $18) 21. Qg3 g6 {Black has no other choice, but now White's attack
is irresistible.} (21... Qg6 22. Qf2) 22. Rcf1 f6 (22... exf4 23. Rxf4 f6 24.
h4 Kh8 25. Nh6 Re7 26. h5 Rg7 27. hxg6 Rxg6 28. Qh4 Rf8 29. Nf5 $18) 23. Ne3 ({
White is winning on the spot after} 23. fxe5 $1 Rxe5 (23... fxe5 24. Nh6+ Kh8
25. Rf7) 24. Nh6+ Kg7 25. Rxf6 $1) 23... exf4 24. Qxf4 (24. Rxf4 Re6 25. h4 $18
) 24... Re6 25. Nd5 Rc8 26. h4 ({Better is} 26. g4 $5 {with the idea g4-g5, to
eliminate the pawn f6 and penetrate on the f-file.}) 26... Kg7 27. h5 Qd6 28.
Qh4 $1 ({In the game White significantly complicated his task after} 28. h6+)
28... g5 29. Qh3 $18 {The black king's position is ruined and now it is much
easier for White to complete his attack.} Rce8 (29... h6 30. Qf5) (29... Kh8
30. Nxf6) (29... Rf8 30. Nxc7) 30. h6+ Kg8 31. b3 c6 32. Ne3 Ne5 33. R3f2 Rf8
34. Nf5 Qd7 35. Ng7 Re7 36. Nh5 $18 *

[Event "Wch U20 Girls 28th"]
[Site "Chotowa"]
[Date "2010.08.05"]
[Round "3"]
[White "Attacking model"]
