{As in the game Hort-Geller, White's bishop on c3 becomes very powerful.} 20.
f4 $1 exf4 21. Rxf4 Qg5 22. Qf2 Nc8 23. Nf5 $1 Re8 ({Black should carefully
arrange his pieces, as there are many hidden tricks like} 23... Nd6 $2 24. Nxg7
$1 $18) 24. Rf1 Nd6 25. h4 {White has a pleasant choice.} (25. Nxg7 $5) (25. g4
$5) 25... Qg6 26. g4 (26. Nxg7 Qxg7 27. Bxf6 Qg6 28. g4 {should also win, but
playing against an engine, Kasparov is not in a hurry to sacrifice.}) 26...
Bxf5 (26... h6 {would be more solid.}) 27. gxf5 Qf7 28. Qf3 (28. Rg1 Kh8 29.
