{White's knight already jumped to f5 and White is in a hurry to join in with
the rest of his army.} 20. f4 $1 exf4 21. Bxf4 Nxf4 22. Rxf4 {It is usually
good for Black to exchange the dangerous knight, but because of his weak
queenside, this defence is not an option here.} c4 (22... Bxf5 23. Rxf5 c4 24.
Qxc7) 23. Raf1 $1 {White is creating very dangerous threats on the f-file.} Be6
{The only way to avoid being crushed.} (23... cxd3 $2 24. Nxg7 $1) (23... f6 $2
24. Nxh6 $1) 24. d4 $1 Bxf5 {There is no choice, as after} (24... Rad8 25. c3
c5 {White has} 26. Nxh6 $1 gxh6 27. d5 Rd7 28. dxe6 Rxe6 29. Qh3 $18) 25. Rxf5
Qd6 {Black is lost anyway.} (25... Rxe4 $2 26. Rxf7 $18) (25... Re7 26. Rxb5
Rxe4 27. Qxc7 $18) (25... f6 26. e5) 26. Qxd6 cxd6 27. R1f4 f6 28. Rxb5 {
, and White easily won the rook endgame.} 1-0

