{White starts the action by exchanging the bishop first.} 13. Nxd6 $1 cxd6 14.
f4 exf4 ({As usual Black prefers to avoid} 14... f6 15. f5 $40) 15. Bxf4 Ng6
16. Bg3 Be6 17. Nc4 $1 {On the way to f5 the knight is attacking the d6-pawn.}
(17. Qf3 d5) 17... Qg5 {Black is trying to defend actively, but it was better
to exchange the knight, avoiding major problems and going into a slightly
worse position.} (17... Bxc4 18. dxc4 Re6 $1 ({Of course not} 18... Rxe4 $6 19.
Rxf7 $1) 19. Qd5 Qc7 20. Rad1 Rd8 21. c3 Ne5 22. b3 $14) 18. Qf3 d5 $6 {
Following the wrong path. It was time for} (18... Ne5 $1 19. Bxe5 dxe5 20. Ne3
$14) 19. Nd6 $1 dxe4 20. dxe4 Re7 21. Nf5 $1 {The knight arrived on f5 with
devastating effect.} (21. Rae1 Ne5 22. Qc3 Nc6 23. e5 Nd4 24. Kh2) 21... Rd7 $6
({The last chance to survive was} 21... Bxf5 22. exf5 Ne5 23. Bxe5 Rxe5 24.
Qxb7 Rae8) 22. h4 $1 {Now Black is helpless.} Qd8 23. h5 Ne7 {or} (23... Bxf5
24. exf5 Nf8 25. h6 $18) 24. Nxg7 $1 $18 Kxg7 25. Qf6+ Kf8 (25... Kg8 26. Be5
$1) 26. Qxe6 Nc6 27. Rad1 $1 Nd4 (27... Rxd1 28. Qxf7#) 28. Bd6+ {, and Black
can't avoid mate} (28. Bd6+ Kg8 29. Qg4+ Kh8 30. Be5+) 1-0

