{Osip Bernstein was the first chessplayer who, already in the first decade of
the 20th century, adopted the delayed Exchange Spanish regularly and revealed
the strategical ideas behind the plan with f2-f4.} 17. f5 $1 {White has no
other way to proceed with accumulating pressure on e5, therefore he fixes the
space advantage with f4-f5. The plan is to follow up with a pawn storm by
g4-g5, challenging the base of Black's pawn chain on g7 and opening the files
for White's rooks to penetrate on the kingside. Because of the doubled pawns
on the queenside, Black has certain difficulties to develop active counterplay
with c5-c4.} Ne7 (17... Nh8 $1 {was more stubborn.} 18. h4 Nf7 19. g4 Be7 20.
Nf3 h6 21. Rg1 Rh8 22. Kf1 c5 {, and Black is well-armed against g4-g5.}) 18.
g4 c5 19. h4 Nc6 20. Nf1 Kd7 {The king comes to help in covering the kingside.}
(20... b5 21. g5 Kb7 22. Kh3 Be7 23. Rg2 c4 24. dxc4 bxc4 25. gxf6 Bxf6 26. Nd2
c3 27. bxc3 Na5 28. h5 h6 29. Rb1+ Kc6 30. Rg6 $18) 21. Ng3 Ke7 22. Rg1 Kf7 23.
Kh3 Be7 24. g5 Rh8 (24... g6 $6 25. Rgf1) (24... Nd4 25. Nh5) 25. Nh5 Rdg8 {
Black managed to build a defensive setup, but White has many options, and it
is just a matter of taste how to break it.} 26. Rfg2 b6 (26... fxg5 27. hxg5 g6
28. Ng3 h6 29. fxg6+ Rxg6 30. Rf1+ Ke6 31. gxh6) 27. gxf6 (27. g6+ {is also
easily winning.} hxg6 28. fxg6+ Ke8 29. Ng3 Kd7 30. h5 Bf8 31. Kg4 Nd8 32. Nf5
Ne6 33. Rh1 a5 34. b3 Kc6 35. Rgh2 Kd7 36. Kf3 Kc6 37. h6 gxh6 38. Bxh6 $18)
27... Bxf6 28. Bh6 g6 (28... gxh6 29. Rxg8 Rxg8 30. Rxg8 Kxg8 31. Nxf6+ Kf7 32.
Nd5 Nd4 (32... Nb4 33. Nxb4 cxb4 34. Kg4 $18) 33. c3 Nf3 34. Nxc7 Ne1 35. Kg4
Nxd3 36. Nd5 Nxb2 37. Nxb6 $18) 29. Nxf6 Kxf6 30. h5 (30. Rf1 $1 Ke7 31. Bg5+
Kd6 32. Bf6) 30... Ne7 31. Bg5+ Kf7 32. Bxe7 $6 {Going for the rook endgame is,
as usual, the most difficult way to convert the advantage.} (32. fxg6+ hxg6 33.
Rf1+ Ke8 34. h6 $18) 32... Kxe7 33. Kh4 Kf7 ({Missing} 33... Rf8 $1 34. Rg5 (
34. fxg6 $6 Rf4+) 34... gxf5 35. exf5 Kf6 36. Rg7 Rf7 37. Rxf7+ Kxf7 38. h6 Kf6
39. Rg7 c4 40. dxc4 Kxf5 41. Rxc7 $18) 34. fxg6+ hxg6 35. Rxg6 Rxg6 36. Rxg6
1-0

