{After the careful preparation of f2-f4 has been made, Black's best defensive
chance was to trade queens. But in the endgame, White's space advantage proved
to be the decisive element.} 18. g3 $1 Nf8 19. f4 exf4 (19... Qd7 $6 20. Qf3)
20. Bxf6 Qxf6 21. gxf4 $1 Qg6 22. f5 $1 (22. Qf3 f5 $1) 22... Qxg4 23. hxg4 f6
$16 {An original pawn structure appeared. White has a huge space advantage and
possibilities to combine the pressure on the kingside ( g4-g5 or Nf4-e6) with
careful preparation of the d3-d4 break. Despite complete lack of counterplay,
Aronian managed to stand and fight until move 60, when he made the decisive
mistake.} *

