1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. Bxc6 dxc6 6. O-O Bg4 $1 (6... Qe7
7. Nbd2 (7. h3 $2 Rg8 $1 $36 {Aronian-Karjakin Berlin 2018}) 7... Bg4 {is the
more frequently seen move order.}) 7. Nbd2 (7. h3 Bh5 8. g4 $6 {is quite
suspicious and should better be avoided. The piece sacrifice is completely
correct:} Nxg4 $1 9. hxg4 Bxg4 10. Be3 Be7 $5 (10... Bd6 11. Kh1 $1 (11. Nbd2
f5 12. exf5 O-O 13. Qe1 Bxf3 14. Nxf3 Rxf5 15. Qe2 Qf6 16. Nh2 e4 17. Qg4 exd3
18. cxd3 Re8 19. Rae1 Re6 20. f4 Qf7 21. Kh1 Rg6 22. Qf3 Qxa2 $13 {Wei,Y -Xiu,
