6. O-O Nd4 $1 7. Bc4 c6 {Naiditsch,A -Nabaty,T Jerusalem ISR 2018}) 6... dxc6
7. Be3 $1 {We have already analysed this position in A) 6 Nc3.} (7. Nxe5 Qd4 8.
Be3 Qxe5 9. d4 Qe7 10. dxc5 Nxe4 11. Qd4 Nxc3 12. Qxc3 Rd8 $11) 7... Bxe3 (7...
Bd6 8. Bg5 $1) (7... Qe7 8. Qd2 Bg4 9. Bxc5 Qxc5 10. O-O-O a5 11. h3 Bxf3 12.
gxf3 a4 13. Rhg1 $40 {Saric,I -Katz,A chess.com INT 2019}) 8. fxe3 Qe7 {
Saric, I -Cheparinov,I chess24.com INT 2020} 9. h3 $14) (5... h6 6. Bxc6 dxc6
7. Ne2 $14) (5... a6 6. Bxc6 dxc6 7. Ne2 Qe7 8. Ng3 O-O 9. O-O $14) 6. Bg5 (6.
Na4 $5 {is another reasonable idea to obtain the bishop pair, but it doesn't
automatically secure an advantage.} Bb6 7. Nxb6 axb6 8. c3 O-O 9. O-O (9. Ba4
d5 $5) 9... Ne7 10. Re1 Ng6 11. d4 Bd7 12. Bd3 Re8 13. Bd2 h6 14. h3 b5 $11)
6... h6 7. Bxf6 (7. Bh4 g5 8. Bg3 Bd7 9. Na4 Bb6 10. Nxb6 axb6 11. h4 g4 12.
