11. Nxc6+ bxc6 12. Qxc5+) 11. Nxg6 Bf7 12. Nce5 $1 hxg6 13. Qxh8 fxe5 14. Bh6
Ne6 (14... Kd7 15. Bxf8 Qxf8 16. Qxe5 Re8 17. Qd4+ Kc8 18. Qe3 Qd6 19. f4 Ne6
20. O-O Nd4 21. Rf2) 15. Bxf8 Nxf8 (15... Kd7 16. Qxe5 Qxf8 17. O-O Re8 18. f4
Kc8 19. Rf2 $16) 16. Qxe5+ $16) 8. Nc4 (8. h4 h5 $1) 8... Bg7 {It is hard to
find a promising continuation for White.} 9. Bd2 O-O 10. O-O b6 11. a4 $5 (11.
Bc3 Qe7 12. a4) 11... a5 (11... c5 12. Qc1 Bb7 13. Bh6 Qe7 (13... f5 $5 14.
Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Nfxe5 Nxe5 16. Nxe5 fxe4 17. dxe4 Qd4 18. Ng4 Qxe4 19. Qh6+ Kg8
20. f3 Qd4+ 21. Qe3 Qxe3+ 22. Nxe3) 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 $11) 12. Bc3 (12. Qc1 Ba6)
12... Qe7 13. Nfd2 Ba6 14. b3 (14. Qf3) (14. Ne3) 14... c5 (14... Rae8) 15. Ne3
f5 $5 16. exf5 gxf5 17. Qh5 Qf7 18. Qxf7+ Rxf7 19. Nec4 Re8 20. Rae1 $14) (7.
b3 {makes no sense here, as Black is in a hurry to play f6 anyway.} f6 8. Nbd2
Nc5 9. Bb2 Bg4 $11) (7. Nc3 $5 Bd6 $1 $11 {After this move I couldn't find
anything substantial. Black's plan is too easy: 0-0, Re8 and Nf8-g6.} (7... f6
8. Nh4 Qe7 9. Nf5 Qf7 10. f4) (7... g6 8. Be3 Bg7 9. Qd2 Qe7 10. Bh6 O-O 11.
