1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 (3... a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. Bxc6 dxc6 6. d3 {is more
or less the same.}) 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. d3 Bd6 $1 (5... Nd7 {is somewhat weaker,
as White is saving a tempo for the prophylactic h2-h3.}) 6. h3 $1 {In my
opinion this is the only idea to fight for an advantage. After any other
continuation, Black plays Bg4. Then after the imminent h3, g4, White has
weakened his kingside, so castling short will not be possible anymore. Black
just castles long and enjoys a good game.} (6. Nbd2 Bg4) (6. Nc3 Bg4 7. h3 Bh5
8. Be3 Qe7 9. a3 O-O-O 10. b4 Nd7 $13) 6... Be6 $1 {The safest way for Black
is to avoid short castling.} (6... c5 7. Nbd2 Qe7 $1 (7... O-O {Early castling
gives White extra options.} 8. a4 $1 (8. Nc4 b5 $1 9. Ne3 c4 $1 (9... Bd7) 10.
a4 cxd3 11. cxd3 b4 12. O-O Ba6 $132) 8... Re8 (8... Be6 9. b3 Nd7 10. Bb2 f6
